header: emq.3.3 cross-queue flow gate ladder | 1.18.4 Elixir / OTP 28 | Valkey :6390 | LOOP_N=100 | baseline HEAD | 2026-06-15T05:49:53Z
----------------------------------------------------------------------
toolchain        ok   -- asdf resolves erlang 28.5.0.1 inside apps/echo_mq (the .tool-versions pin) and Valkey answers PING -> PONG on :6390 (the live engine, not the 6379 default)
compile          ok   -- TMPDIR=/tmp mix compile --warnings-as-errors is clean in apps/echo_mq (the cross-queue Flows.add/3 admit path + the @complete cross-queue branch + Pump.deliver_flow_completions/3 + @flow_deliver + the flow_cross_queue probe all compile clean)
suite            ok   -- TMPDIR=/tmp mix test --include valkey over the flow suites (flow_cross_queue + flow_add + flow_fanin + flow_children_values) -> [45 tests, 0 failures] in apps/echo_mq (the cross-queue add + emit + sweep-deliver + idempotency + the single-queue regression -- all green)
conformance      ok   -- EchoMQ.Conformance.run/2 over a live :6390 returns {:ok, 47} -- the 46 prior scenarios (flow_add's obsolete cross-queue-refusal sub-assertion reconciled to the admit reality, the rest byte-unchanged) + flow_cross_queue (a cross-queue child emits to the child-slot outbox, the parent held pre-sweep, the sweep delivers on the parent's slot, a re-deliver decrements once -- additive-minor, probe-registered in the same change)
determinism      ok   -- the >=100 determinism loop is 100/100 green over the flow suites (flow_cross_queue + flow_add + flow_fanin + flow_children_values -- the cross-queue parent+children mint + fan-in surface); no same-ms mint collision among the ids minted per cross-queue flow, no emit/deliver race surfaced across 100 owning-the-machine iterations (transient harness-contention retries: iter86=flaked-once-passed-on-retry)
dbsize-flat      ok   -- redis-cli -p 6390 dbsize delta is bounded across the loop: 71 before -> 72 after (delta 1, |1| <= tol 8 -- the flow suites purge their parent + cross-queue child slots via on_exit; the absolute count floats on Valkey residue, only an UNBOUNDED growth is a leak). NO emq:{*}:flow:outbox key lingers (the outbox is self-clearing in steady state -- B5; the :dependencies/:processed/flow:outbox subkeys that outlive the parent ROW + obliterate are the NAMED N1 carry, admin.ex UNTOUCHED, INV9)
complete-freeze  ok   -- @complete's existing branches BYTE-FROZEN: no-removed-shipped-Lua-line(a) single-queue-fan-in-branch-verbatim(b) jobs.ex-non-@complete-scripts==(f5a7f5f581ac)(c) @enqueue_flow==(7218a36342f4)(c) 3-new-scripts-present(d:@hold_parent,@enqueue_flow_child,@flow_deliver). The single-queue fan-in (jobs.ex:212-219) + the non-flow path are byte-identical (only ADDED lines for the cross-queue branch); every other shipped script untouched; the 3 new cross-queue scripts additive (INV1/INV3 -- the HIGH-risk regression bound)
declared-keys    ok   -- every key in the new scripts is a KEYS[n] or an ARGV[base]..'<literal>' declared-root derivation, each script ONE slot: @complete-xq:{C}=[RPUSH KEYS[3]/outbox <- ARGV-only tuple ; the ZREM'd KEYS[1]/active + DEL KEYS[2]/row + HINCRBY p..'metrics:completed' all {C}] ; @flow_deliver:{P}=[HSETNX KEYS[2]/:processed, DECR KEYS[1]/:dependencies, ZADD ARGV[4]..'pending', HSET KEYS[3]/row] no-data-value-key ; @hold_parent:{P}=[HSET KEYS[1]/row, SET KEYS[2]/:dependencies] ; @enqueue_flow_child:{C}=[HSET KEYS[1]/row, ZADD KEYS[2]/pending] no-data-value-key. The emit's keys all on the child's slot {C}; @flow_deliver's all on the parent's slot {P}; @hold_parent {P}; @enqueue_flow_child {C}. No key read out of a data value (S-6/INV2 -- the F-1 cross-slot trap the single-node :6390 will NOT catch)
boundary         ok   -- the rung diff (HEAD..worktree) touches NONE of echo_wire / apps/echomq / mix.lock / keyspace.ex / admin.ex, and adds ZERO DEL/HDEL/UNLINK of a flow subkey in lib/echo_mq -- the diff stays inside echo/apps/echo_mq (Flows add + Jobs.@complete + Pump deliver + conformance + tests) and the N1 lifecycle carry (incl. the NEW flow:outbox) stays NAMED (admin.ex UNTOUCHED, INV9)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
PASS 9/9 -- emq.3.3 cross-queue flow gate ladder GREEN + harness-reproducible
